column5: quit smoking and havn t look back
A New Years Resolution that took an extra week. Good on you for beating it, don't ever look back.
From a guy who is watching his father fade away with COPD all I can say is well done!!! You have dodged a very very undesirable bullet.
Cant remember if its six or seven years for myself but ya never looked back
16 years come this May, and I have not missed it for a moment.
A friend died a month ago from lung cancer after smoking for many years. He suffered greatly at the end. It is not worth it!
My wife and I quit smoking When our first grandchild was born, we knew that it was time to stop. Grand daughter will be 20 in June.

Congrats. I did it a few years back and it was one of  the best decisions I ever made. For a while I bought stuff for myself from the $ I saved. If I'd kept account I'm sure it would easily pay for any expensive fishing eqpt that I've bought.
23 for me. Best thing I have done.
Excellent. Dumbest thing I ever spent $$$ on...
Almost 3 years for me and I'll never go back
14 months for me.Still get the odd craving, but got it beat.
i just quit for the first time and made it 4 months started again over the holidays,  today is my first day smoke free again .

i just quit for the first time and made it 4 months started again over the holidays,  today is my first day smoke free again . My brother quit and started up again 3 times before he actually beat it. He hasn't smoked for nearly 25 years now.  Keep at it. You will be glad you did.

My brother has quit and started 3 times, each time its going to the bars with friends who smoke that start up the habits again and he gives in over the evening then its back to the convenience store when he wakes up to scratch the itch
